<h1 class="hero-h">Fractional CMO Denver: <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">senior marketing leadership for operators here.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Treetop works with B2B mid-market companies in Denver and across Colorado. If you're a founder or CEO between $3M and $30M ARR considering a fractional CMO, here's the Denver-specific context and engagement model.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Treetop offers fractional CMO services in Denver, CO. Engagements run $8K-$25K/month for B2B companies needing senior marketing leadership without a full-time hire. Remote-first with quarterly in-person on-site for Denver clients when scope warrants.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Denver's B2B market context</h2>
<p class="body">Denver's B2B ecosystem in 2026 is centered around B2B SaaS, fintech, aerospace tech, energy tech, healthcare tech, outdoor industry SaaS. For fractional CMO engagements specifically, this means:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Buyer rhythm matches the industries above. Sales cycles, evaluation patterns, and decision-maker profiles vary by sector.</li>
<li>Talent market for senior fractional operators is meaningful. You have real options without paying coastal-tier rates.</li>
<li>Most B2B buyers in Denver want substance over hype. Marketing that lands here translates well elsewhere.</li>
<li>Pipeline rhythm rewards consistency more than peaks. Quarterly cadence beats one-off campaigns.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Treetop's Denver engagement model</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Remote-first with quarterly on-site.</strong> Quarterly in-person leadership offsites for Denver engagements where scope warrants.</li>
<li><strong>1-2 days per week typical.</strong> Fractional means fractional. Defined cadence, not always-on.</li>
<li><strong>Builder profile.</strong> We ship work; we don't just present strategy.</li>
<li><strong>AI-fluent.</strong> Modern fractional CMO work compounds with AI workflows. We bring those.</li>
<li><strong>12-18 month engagements</strong> typical for compounding outcomes.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Scope of work typically includes: strategy, positioning, demand generation, content, brand, team leadership.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to consider Treetop specifically</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You're a B2B founder/CEO at $3M-$30M ARR.</li>
<li>You're in Denver or open to a remote-first engagement with quarterly on-site.</li>
<li>You want senior marketing leadership without a $300K+ full-time hire.</li>
<li>You want a fractional CMO who personally uses AI tooling, not just talks about it.</li>
<li>You can commit $8K-$25K/month for 12-18 months.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional CMO vs. agency vs. full-time hire: what Denver B2B companies choose</h2>
<p class="body">The three most common options for B2B companies between $3M and $30M ARR each serve a different situation.</p>
<div class="compare-grid">
<div class="compare-cell hd">Option</div>
<div class="compare-cell hd">Best fit</div>
<div class="compare-cell hd">Watch out for</div>
<div class="compare-cell"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">Fractional CMO</strong></div>
<div class="compare-cell">You need strategy ownership and leadership, not just execution. You want one accountable operator who builds the system.</div>
<div class="compare-cell">Not a fit if you only need one specific tactic (paid ads, SEO) with no broader strategy need.</div>
<div class="compare-cell"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">Marketing agency</strong></div>
<div class="compare-cell">You have a defined channel (paid search, content, PR) and want specialists to execute it well.</div>
<div class="compare-cell">Agencies rarely own strategy. Without a CMO-level operator above them, they optimize for their channel, not your revenue.</div>
<div class="compare-cell"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">Full-time CMO hire</strong></div>
<div class="compare-cell">You're past $30M ARR, need a full-time presence, and have budget for $250K+ total comp plus equity.</div>
<div class="compare-cell">Long ramp time (3-6 months before meaningful output). High cost if the fit is wrong. Usually premature below $30M ARR.</div>
</div>
<p class="body">Most Denver B2B companies in the $5M-$20M range get the best return from a fractional CMO to lead strategy, plus one or two agency partners to execute specific channels underneath that leadership.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How much does a fractional CMO cost in Denver?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Fractional CMO engagements in Denver typically run $8,000 to $25,000 per month depending on scope and time commitment. That compares to $250,000 to $350,000 per year for a full-time CMO hire (salary, benefits, equity). Most Treetop engagements run 12 to 18 months.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with companies in Denver?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. Treetop works remotely with B2B mid-market clients in Denver and across Colorado. In-person quarterly on-site available for Denver-based clients when scope warrants.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Are you based in Denver?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Treetop is based in Austin, TX. We work with clients across the US remotely, with in-person quarterly on-site sessions available when warranted.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is a fractional CMO better than a marketing agency for a Denver B2B company?</h3><p class="faq-qa">For most B2B companies at $3M-$30M ARR, yes: a fractional CMO owns strategy end-to-end rather than executing a single channel. The two can work together well. A fractional CMO leads the strategy layer; agencies execute specific channels underneath that leadership.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What industries does Treetop serve in Denver?</h3><p class="faq-qa">B2B SaaS, fintech, energy tech, healthcare tech, aerospace tech, outdoor industry, and professional services. The common thread is B2B revenue models between $3M and $30M ARR that need senior marketing leadership without a full-time hire.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How quickly can a fractional CMO deliver results?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Most clients see early positioning and pipeline improvements within 60 to 90 days. Month one is diagnostics and quick wins. By month three, a demand generation cadence is running. Compounding results build over 12 to 18 months as positioning sharpens and channels mature.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How do I start an engagement?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Get an AI CMO Starter Report for $99: live competitive data, keyword gaps, and a 90-day roadmap. The AI Audit produces a written, prioritized roadmap in 5 business days and is the most common starting point.</p></div>
</div></section>

